title: For Sale:  1924/30 Venezuela FN Mauser w/AAA Wood NR
postcontent: Of all the military rifles made in the last 100 or so years, I think that the Mausers made for South American countries in the 20th Century are some of the prettiest. This is “old world craftsmanship” at its very best! After World War I, Germany was forbidden from manufacturing military firearms. FN, using Paul Mauser’s excellent design for the Model 1898, manufactured this model at their factory in Herstel, Belgium, one of the world’s great armories and where top grade Brownings are made today. There are Belgian proofmarks on the bolt handle and front receiver ring. Our example is serial number 5726 and that number appears on the stock, receiver and bolt handle. The barrel and most metal parts still retain about 99.5% of their original bright blue. The receiver and bolt are polished bright. The bore is mint and looks unfired, bright and shiny with razor sharp rifling. To top it off, there are lots of traces of original armory grease in protected areas. The bolt release lever is brilliantly fire blued. The front receiver ring is beautifully impressed with the Venezuelan coat of arms. The stock is absolutely beautiful and with its highly figured, deep honey color wood looks like it should be on a high grade hunting rifle. No cracks or splits with its entire original military finish remaining. All markings in the metal and wood are excellent. No import marks that I can find.
